data.name: transformations
data.description: transformations is a list of transformations that need to be applied. It is expressed as list of functions of there are parameters for the function they can be give out in round brackets in name=value format. For example, if you want to resize, rotate by 90-degrees and sharpen the transformations would be: Transformations =resize(height=200),rotate(degrees=90),sharpen As many transformations as required can be applied in a single request. The order of application is the same as the order of the list inputted. The end result will be a single image. If no parameters are given for a particular transformation, default parameters are taken.

This function can apply mutiple tranformations in a single request. The transformations have to be given in a comma aperated list. Parameters to each of the transformations can be passed in a round brackets.

data.description: width of cropped image in pixels. If its less than one its taken as a proportion of original width.

Function to crop images. Parameters are img, height, width,aspect_ratio, auto_center,left, top, center, middle. If auto_center is not set as false position of cropping can be given by left and top or center (horizontal positionings) and middle (vertical positioning). If any of these values are less than 1, they will be calculated as a percentage of absolute values.  If auto_center is true, cropping will be done to show most significant part of the image.  If height is less than 1, height will be calculated as a percent. If width is less than 1, width will be calculated as a percent. If both height and width are given then aspect ratio is ignored, Default value for aspect ratio is 1.0.

data.name: thumbify

description:
Process and serve beautiful images on the fly. No need to store multiple copies of the same image. Apply all the transformations to the master image on the fly and serve to the client. Optimize the image delivery time. 
img api is a clean and easy to use api to process images on the fly and render them to the clients. You can :

    crop images
    resize images
    optimize images to suit the screen
    enhance images: sharpen, blur, brighten etc.
    apply funky filters to images
    rotate and flip
    generate thumbnails
    and much more…
